  "stimulus": "The functions $f$ and $g$ are twice differentiable. The table shown gives values of the functions and their first derivatives at selected values of $x$.\n\n| $x$ | 0 | 2 | 4 | 7 |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| $f(x)$ | 10 | 7 | 4 | 5 |\n| $f'(x)$ | $\\frac{3}{2}$ | $-8$ | 3 | 6 |\n| $g(x)$ | 1 | 2 | $-3$ | 0 |\n| $g'(x)$ | 5 | 4 | 2 | 8 |",
  "stimulus_image": null,
  "documents": null,
  "parts": [
    {
      "letter": "a",
      "prompt": "Let $h$ be the function defined by $h(x) = f(g(x))$. Find $h'(7)$. Show the work that leads to your answer.",
      "point_value": 2,
      "scoring_notes": "Chain rule form earns first point. Answer of $12$ earns second point only if chain rule was applied. Without chain rule setup, second point requires showing $f'(0) \\cdot 8 = 12$ or $\\frac{3}{2} \\cdot 8$. Unsupported answer of $12$ earns no points.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "a1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Applies chain rule",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Applies chain rule"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(x) = f'(g(x)) \\cdot g'(x)$"
            }
          ],
          "wrong_examples": [
            "earns no points"
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "a2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct answer",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct answer"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(7) = f'(g(7)) \\cdot g'(7) = f'(0) \\cdot 8 = \\frac{3}{2} \\cdot 8 = 12$"
            }
          ],
          "wrong_examples": [
            "earns no points"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "b",
      "prompt": "Let $k$ be a differentiable function such that $k'(x) = (f(x))^2 \\cdot g(x)$. Is the graph of $k$ concave up or concave down at the point where $x = 4$? Give a reason for your answer.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": "First point earned for correct differentiation form (product + chain rule). A single error in applying product or chain rule still earns first point, but prevents second point. Third point consistent with any declared nonzero value of $k''(4)$.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "b1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Applies product rule (and chain rule)",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Applies product rule (and chain rule)"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$k''(x) = 2f(x) \\cdot f'(x) \\cdot g(x) + (f(x))^2 \\cdot g'(x)$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct value",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct value"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$k''(4) = 2(4)(3)(-3) + (4)^2(2) = -72 + 32 = -40$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Concave down at $x = 4$ because $k''(4) = -40 < 0$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Concave down at $x = 4$ because $k''(4) = -40 < 0$"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "c",
      "prompt": "Let $m$ be the function defined by $m(x) = 5x^3 + \\int_0^x f'(t)\\, dt$. Find $m(2)$. Show the work that leads to your answer.",
      "point_value": 1,
      "scoring_notes": "Must show supporting work equivalent to $5 \\cdot 8 + (f(2) - f(0))$ or $40 + (7 - 10)$. Unsupported answer of $37$ earns no credit. Uses FTC: $\\int_0^2 f'(t)\\, dt = f(2) - f(0) = 7 - 10 = -3$.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "c1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct answer with supporting work",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct answer with supporting work"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$m(2) = 5(8) + \\int_0^2 f'(t)\\, dt = 40 + (f(2) - f(0)) = 40 + (7 - 10) = 37$"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
